  "prompt": "I deleted my friend ID from WeChat. How do I find it again?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, if you've deleted a friend's WeChat ID from your contacts, **there's no built-in way to directly recover it within WeChat.** Once the contact is gone, the ID is gone too.\n\nHere are your options for finding it again, ranked from most likely to least likely to be successful:\n\n*   **Ask your mutual friends:** This is the easiest and most likely to work. If you have mutual friends with the person you deleted, ask them to share your friend's WeChat ID with you.\n\n*   **Check old chat groups:** If you were both in the same WeChat group(s), you might be able to find their WeChat ID there. Look through the group members list.\n\n*   **Check old chat history (if you haven't cleared it):** If you haven't cleared your chat history, scroll back through old conversations. They might have mentioned their ID in a message, or it might be visible in an older contact card they sent.\n\n*   **Contact them through other means:** If you have their phone number, email address, or another social media account, try contacting them through those channels to ask for their WeChat ID.\n\n*   **Reverse search their phone number:** This only works if they have their WeChat linked to their phone number and their privacy settings allow it. You can try adding their phone number as a contact in your phone, and see if WeChat suggests adding them.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Privacy:** Be mindful of privacy. Don't ask mutual friends to share someone's contact information without first getting their consent.\n*   **Data Security:** Be cautious of any third-party services that claim to recover deleted WeChat contacts. These services are often scams or can compromise your account security.\n\nIn summary, finding the WeChat ID again will rely on alternative methods of contacting your friend or searching for it within your existing connections and data.\n",
